orm their extended Ly-alpha emission line halos. The\nstarburst and AGN activity in these galaxies are thus combining to produce an\neffective and wide-spread \"feedback\" process, acting on the long-term gas\nreservoir for the galaxy. If episodic radio activity and co-eval starbursts are\ncommon in massive, high-z galaxies, then this IC-feedback mechanism may affect\nthe star-formation histories of massive galaxies. [Abridged]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Oct 2012 20:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-11"}
