r$-partite hypergraphs.\nFinally, we show that no optimal edge-discriminator on any hypergraph $\\mathcal\nH=(\\mathcal V, \\mathcal E)$, with $|\\mathcal E|=n (\\geq 3)$, satisfies\n$\\sum_{v\\in \\mathcal V} \\lambda_\\mathcal H (v)=n(n+1)/2-1$, which, in turn,\nraises many other interesting combinatorial questions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Oct 2012 08:38:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 22 Nov 2012 22:29:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-08-12"}
